      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/169/5716",
      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ مُسْلِمٍ قُتِلَ وَ لَهُ أَبٌ نَصْرَانِيٌّ لِمَنْ تَكُونُ دِيَتُهُ قَالَ \"تُؤْخَذُ فَتُجْعَلُ فِي بَيْتِ مَالِ اَلْمُسْلِمِينَ لِأَنَّ جِنَايَتَهُ عَلَى بَيْتِ مَالِ اَلْمُسْلِمِينَ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5716 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Malik ibn Atiyyah from Sulayman ibn Khalid from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a Muslim man who was killed and had a Christian father.\nImam (as) was asked: \"To whom does his blood money (diyyah) go?\"\nImam (as) said: \"It is taken and placed in the treasury (Bayt Al-Mal) of the Muslims because his liability falls upon the treasury of the Muslims.\""
        ]
      }
    },
